Second Gentleman Douglas Emhoff will be attending the World Economic Forum Annual Meeting in Davos, Switzerland, from January 17 to January 20. During his time there, he will emphasize the Biden-Harris Administration's commitment to addressing Antisemitism, Islamophobia, and all forms of hate. He will also participate in events centered on promoting gender equality and protecting women's rights. Mr. Emhoff will meet with government officials and private sector leaders to discuss these matters, furthering his efforts to combat hate, promote unity, collaboration, and tackle gender inequality.